7. Future Work

7.1 Self‑Healing Systems

Beyond detection, BE‑AI could become part of a self‑healing ecosystem. When an epistemic contradiction is detected, the system could automatically generate a patch that removes the contradictory behavior or quarantines the package.

7.2 Decentralized Trust Networks

The provenance layer could be extended to include trust signals from distributed ledgers, enabling verifiable reputation without central authorities.

7.3 Integration into AI Operating Systems

As part of the TS‑AI‑OS vision, BE‑AI could become the native trust monitor for all software running on the OS. The kernel would enforce behavioral policies derived from intent, blocking any operation that contradicts declared intent.

7.4 Adversarial Robustness

Future work will investigate how adversaries could fool BE‑AI by manipulating intent extraction (e.g., adding benign‑sounding documentation) and develop robust intent inference techniques.

