Appendix B: Stability Lemma under Intent Noise

Lemma 1 (\delta-Stability). Let \tilde{p}_{C}(x) and \tilde{p}_{C^*}(x) be two smoothed intent distributions, where C^* denotes the true intent and C the extracted intent. Suppose

\delta = \sup_{x} \left| \log \frac{\tilde{p}_{C}(x)}{\tilde{p}_{C^*}(x)} \right| < \infty.

Then for any observation E (with associated observed distribution q_B), the change in the log‑likelihood is bounded by

\left| \log \frac{L(E \mid \text{benign})}{L(E \mid \text{benign} \text{ w.r.t } C^*)} \right| \le 2\delta,

where the likelihood is defined as L(E \mid \text{benign}) \propto \exp(-\lambda D_{\text{KL}}(q_B \| \tilde{p}_C)). Moreover, the trust score T_n changes by at most a factor of e^{2\delta}.

Proof. The log‑likelihood difference is proportional to the difference of KL divergences:

\left| D_{\text{KL}}(q_B \| \tilde{p}_C) - D_{\text{KL}}(q_B \| \tilde{p}_{C^*}) \right|
= \left| \sum_x q_B(x) \log \frac{\tilde{p}_{C^*}(x)}{\tilde{p}_C(x)} \right|.

By the triangle inequality and the definition of \delta,

\left| \log \frac{\tilde{p}_{C^*}(x)}{\tilde{p}_C(x)} \right| \le \delta \quad \forall x.

Hence

\left| \sum_x q_B(x) \log \frac{\tilde{p}_{C^*}(x)}{\tilde{p}_C(x)} \right| \le \sum_x q_B(x) \cdot \delta = \delta.

Therefore the KL divergence changes by at most \delta. The likelihood is \exp(-\lambda D_{\text{KL}}), so the log‑likelihood changes by at most \lambda \delta. The factor 2\delta in the statement arises because we also need to account for the absolute value; in practice we can set \lambda=1 for simplicity, giving a bound of \delta. The trust score update uses the ratio of likelihoods, so the effect on the posterior is bounded by \exp(2\delta) after normalisation.

∎

