Appendix G: Evaluation Metrics and Statistical Testing

G.1 Metrics

· True Positive Rate (TPR) at 1% False Positive Rate (FPR). We compute the decision threshold that yields FPR = 1% on the validation set, then report TPR on the test set.
· Area Under the ROC Curve (AUC).
· Time‑to‑detection: The number of runtime events (or seconds) until the package is flagged.
· Explainability: SHAP values for the inconsistency score.

G.2 Statistical Significance

We will use bootstrap resampling (10,000 iterations) to compute 95% confidence intervals for TPR and AUC. For pairwise comparisons (e.g., BE‑AI vs. PyGuard), we will use McNemar’s test on a matched test set to assess whether differences are significant at p < 0.05.

