Appendix H: Implementation Details and Hyperparameters

H.1 LLM Fine‑Tuning

· Base model: CodeLlama‑7B.
· Fine‑tuning dataset: 50,000 manually annotated packages (each with a list of capabilities and confidence weights). Annotations obtained via a combination of expert labeling and semi‑automated extraction from documentation.
· Quantization: 4‑bit (bitsandbytes) for inference.
· Output: JSON with capabilities and a confidence score per capability.

H.2 VGAE Architecture

· GIN encoder: 3 layers, hidden dimension 128, output dimension 64.
· MLP for \mu and \log\sigma^2: 2 layers, hidden 64, output 32.
· Decoder: bilinear product with 32‑dimensional node embeddings.
· Training: Adam optimizer, learning rate 0.001, batch size 128, 100 epochs.
· Regularization: \beta = 0.1 for the KL term.

H.3 Sandbox Configuration

· Container: Docker with seccomp profile restricting dangerous syscalls.
· Tracing: eBPF via bpftrace scripts that record events and map them to ontology.
· Timeout: 5 minutes per package (or until all code paths are exercised via simple tests).

H.4 Fusion Weights

The weights \lambda_{\text{KL}}, \lambda_{W_1}, \lambda_{\text{latent}} will be tuned on a validation set via grid search to maximize TPR@1%FPR.

